data.description: Gorgeous custom home on 73 acres! Want to live the Country Life? This is the spot for you! With plenty of land to build, explore, hunt and just enjoy, this property has a lot to offer. Starting with a spacious 1970 sqft home that features 3 bedrooms and two full baths and has the desirable split floor plan with master suite on one side of the home with two guest bedrooms and a full bath on the other. The center of the home is open for excellent flow to make both entertaining and everyday living the best it can be. A huge kitchen with plentiful cabinets affords both storage and convenience for the new owner. Ceramic tile throughout means easy living and easy clean up. The master suite consists of an oversized bedroom with large walk in closet and attached bathroom with both a shower and clawfoot bathtub. On the same wing is a once home office/den that has been converted into a massive closet and dressing space for those with abundant clothes and shoes. The home has both front and back covered patios for front porch swinging and backyard BBQ'ing. A concrete cistern in the backyard was once a glistening above ground pool and could be again with some upkeep. Pump and electrical, water connections still in place. Also out back you will find a volleyball court as well as a barn and workshop area complete with power and window unit for cooling. Space to store you items, attend to your hobbies and keep your RV or tractor out of the Texas sun. On the East side of the property there are electrical, water and septic connections in place where once sat an RV next to a dug pond just waiting for the included liner to be installed and filled with water. To the Southwest, the owner has selectively cleared a second homesite with water lines ran, but left many ornamental mesquites in place for an excellent backyard view. Hunting is not only allowed, but encouraged down here in the Golden Triangle area as Whitetail deer grow to record sizes, wild hogs, turkey and dove are also plentiful. Some cross fencing is in place in case you want to bring in some large animals. Total travel time to HEB or Walmart is less than 8 minutes. So your ice cream is still cold when you get home!
